cs.DS, cs.CG, cs.GT, cs.DM, cs.CC. 

The paper deals with algorithms for computing minimum cuts in undirected surface-embedded graphs, which involves topics such as graph theory, computational geometry, and combinatorial optimization. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) are likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the complexity of the problem and proves NP-hardness, which suggests that cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) are also possible sub-categories.
